or%20terrorism%2C%20organized%20crime%2C%20and%20crimes%20against%20Women%20and%20Children.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex%20Supreme%20Court%20Judge%20On%20Master%20Of%20Roster%20Business%20And%20Case%20Allocation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWading%20into%20a%20legal%20minefield%2C%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Kurian%20Joseph%20Saturday%20pitched%20for%20an%20expanded%20mechanism%20including%20at%20least%20three%20judges%20to%20decide%20allocation%20of%20cases%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20to%20end%20the%20public%20perception%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bmaster%20of%20roster%20business%26quot%3B%20is%20not%20being%20handled%20the%20way%20it%20should%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20had%20in%20a%202018%20judgment%20said%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bmaster%20of%20the%20roster%26quot%3B%20and%20there%20is%20no%20dispute%20that%20he%20has%20the%20%26quot%3Bultimate%20authority%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bprerogative%26quot%3B%20to%20allocate%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20main%20observation%20I%20made%20after%20my%20retirement%20also%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20perception%20of%20a%20remote%20control%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20So%2C%20there%20is%20a%20perception%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20public%20that%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20business%20is%20not%20handled%20the%20way%20it%20should%20be%20handled%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20my%20first%20suggestion%20on%20that%20master%20of%20roster%20business%20is%20that%20it%20should%20be%20done%20at%20least%20by%20three%20(judges)%2C%20and%20on%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20benches%2C%20particularly%20very%20important%20constitutional%20matters%2C%20the%20diversity%20should%20be%20reflected%20--%20regional%2C%20gender%20--%20at%20least%20these%20two%20should%20be%20reflected%20in%20constituting%20the%20benches%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Joseph%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20one%20of%20the%20four%20most%20senior%20apex%20court%20judges%20who%20had%20held%20an%20unprecedented%20press%20conference%20in%20January%202018%20where%20they%20raised%20several%20issues%20including%20about%20assignment%20of%20cases%20in%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20a%20seminar%20organised%20by%20the%20Campaign%20for%20Judicial%20Accountability%20and%20Reforms%20(CJAR)%2C%20Justice%20Joseph%20said%20after%20that%20press%20conference%2C%20a%20series%20of%20meetings%20of%20the%20incoming%20chief%20justices%20with%20the%20four%20judges%20took%20place%20and%20there%20was%20one%20suggestion%20that%20the%20master%20of%20roster%20exercise%20should%20be%20appropriately%20regulated%2C%20not%20controlled%2C%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20any%20perceived%20arbitrariness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20apex%20court%20judge%20launched%20a%20frontal%20attack%20on%20the%20media%20for%20having%20failed%20to%20defend%20democracy%20and%20the%20Constitution%20as%20he%20made%20a%20spirited%20call%20for%20protecting%20whistle-blowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20find%20any%20fearless%2C%20truthful%20version%20of%20the%20facts%20coming%20out.%20The%20greatest%20blow%20to%20democracy%20is%20that%20the%20fourth%20pillar%20has%20failed%20the%20country.%20Forget%20about%20the%20first%20three%20pillars.%20The%20fourth%20pillar%20is%20the%20media%20and%20they%20have%20failed%20to%20defend%20democracy.%20They%20have%20failed%20to%20defend%20the%20Constitution.%20They%20have%20failed%20to%20defend%20the%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20our%20only%20hope%20is%20the%20fifth%20pillar%2C%20whistle%20blowers.%20Somehow%20they%20are%20also%20not%20able%20to%20blow%2C%20maybe%20post%20COVID%20lungs%20have%20been%20affected.%20The%20way%20the%20lungs%20are%20crushed%20in%20the%20country%20today%20so%20that%20nobody%20will%20blow%20the%20whistle%20is%20a%20very%20dangerous%20trend%20for%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20advised%20constitutional%20courts%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20equal%20importance%20has%20to%20be%20given%20to%20both%20aspects%20of%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution-life%20and%20liberty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20taking%20away%20the%20liberty%20part%20of%20a%20person%2C%20there%20is%20no%20point%20in%20giving%20him%20the%20life%20part.%20So%2C%20I%20think%2C%20I%20am%20of%20the%20strong%20view%20that%20our%20constitutional%20courts%20should%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20Article%2021%20should%20be%20understood%20giving%20equal%20importance%20to%20both%20aspects%20of%20life%20and%20liberty%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20perception%20now%20is%20that%20life%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20guarded%20but%20liberty%20is%20ignored%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Joseph%20said%20while%20addressing%20the%20gathering%20at%20the%20first%20session%20of%20the%20seminar%20on%20'Supreme%20Court%20Administration%20and%20Management%3A%C2%93%20Issues%20and%20Concerns'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20Justice%20Joseph%2C%20former%20apex%20court%20judge%20Justice%20Madan%20B%20Lokur%2C%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20Justice%20Rekha%20Sharma%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Meenakshi%20Arora%2C%20and%20advocates%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20and%20Kamini%20Jaiswal%20also%20addressed%20the%20gathering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObserving%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20always%20been%20considered%20and%20conceived%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bguardian%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20he%20said%20judges%20take%20oath%20that%20they%20will%20uphold%20the%20Constitution%20and%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20judges%20speaking%20'I%20have%20done%20best%20according%20to%20my%20conscience'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20no%20special%20and%20individual%20conscience.%20His%20conscience%20is%20only%20the%20constitutional%20conscience.%20He%20is%20the%20conscience-keeper%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Joseph%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20trend%20now%20is%20if%20a%20case%20is%20posted%20to%20a%20bench%2C%20people%20are%20able%20to%20predict%20what%20the%20result%20would%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Joseph%20was%20elevated%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20March%208%2C%202013%20and%20retired%20on%20November%2029%2C%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20that%2C%20he%20became%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Kerala%20High%20Court%20in%20July%202000%20and%20was%20later%20elevated%20as%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708780020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fcq5c2cmg_supreme-court-reuters_625x300_06_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fex-supreme-court-judge-kurian-joseph-on-master-of-roster-business-and-case-allocation-5119053%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Kurian%20Joseph%20Saturday%20pitched%20for%20an%20expanded%20mechanism%20including%20at%20least%20three%20judges%20to%20decide%20allocation%20of%20cases%20in%20the%20apex%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fex-supreme-court-judge-kurian-joseph-on-master-of-roster-business-and-case-allocation-5119053%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fex-supreme-court-judge-kurian-joseph-on-master-of-roster-business-and-case-allocation-5119053%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fex-supreme-court-judge-kurian-joseph-on-master-of-roster-business-and-case-allocation-5119053%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Oregon%20is%20giving%20homeless%20young%20people%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20to%20get%20back%20on%20their%20feet.%20Here's%20how%20it's%20going.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20outreach%20supervisor%20with%20the%204D%20Recovery%20Center%2C%20speaks%20to%20a%20person%20in%20a%20tent%20about%20services%20for%20those%20experiencing%20homelessness%20and%20treatment%20for%20fentanyl%20addiction%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bfd6707a3d2714887777e5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20outreach%20supervisor%20speaks%20to%20a%20person%20in%20a%20tent%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOregon%20is%20giving%20some%20of%20its%20homeless%20youth%20%241%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20state's%20DHS%20says%20recipients%20report%20spending%20money%20on%20housing%20and%20food.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20program%20is%20among%20dozens%20nationwide%20trying%20to%20alleviate%20poverty%20with%20a%20guaranteed%20basic%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOregon%20has%20a%20severe%20homelessness%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20home%20to%20the%20third-worst%20homeless%20rate%20in%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20a%20federal%20count%20published%20in%20December.%20And%20it%20has%20the%20highest%20rate%20anywhere%20of%20unaccompanied%20homeless%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20state%20leaders%20scramble%20to%20address%20the%20problem%2C%20one%20solution%20is%20showing%20some%20promise%3A%20Give%20those%20young%20people%20%241%2C000%20cash%20every%20month%2C%20no%20strings%20attached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Oregon%20Department%20of%20Human%20Services%20launched%20its%20Direct%20Cash%20Transfer%20Plus%20Pilot%20in%20February%202022.%20The%20program%20targets%20homeless%20people%20between%2018%20to%2024%20who%20have%20an%20%26quot%3Bintention%20to%20become%20housed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DHS%20wrote%20last%20year%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oregon.gov%2Fodhs%2Fabout%2Flegislativeinformation%2F2023-ors-417-799-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20report%20on%20youth%20homelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20120%20young%20people%20across%20the%20state%20are%20receiving%20the%20direct%20cash%20payments%2C%20the%20report%20says.%20About%2075%20of%20the%20recipients%20are%20in%20Multnomah%20County%2C%20home%20to%20Portland.%20Initial%20payments%20for%20participants%20in%20the%20program%20started%20in%20February%202023%20and%20are%20scheduled%20to%20run%20until%20January%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParticipants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-works-red-state-blue-state-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceive%20payments%20of%20%24%201%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fa%3E%20They%20can%20also%20receive%20a%20one-time%20%243%2C000%20%26quot%3Benrichment%20fund%26quot%3B%20payment.%20The%20program%20started%20implementing%20the%20larger%20payment%20after%20conversations%20with%20participants%20who%20said%20they%20still%20had%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20financial%20obstacles%26quot%3B%20after%20receiving%20initial%20payments%20from%20the%20program%2C%20the%20document%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20qualification%20for%20the%20program%20is%20to%20be%20a%20young%20person%20who%20is%20unhoused%2C%20though%20there%20are%20other%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20like%20being%20a%20member%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20%E2%80%94%20that%20can%20give%20applicants%20priority.%C2%A0There%20are%20no%20limits%20on%20how%20participants%20spend%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecipients%20said%20they%20spent%20the%20funds%20mostly%20on%20housing%2C%20repairing%20vehicles%2C%20furniture%2C%20and%20moving%20costs%2C%20the%20DHS%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20more%20than%2065%25%20of%20the%20participants%20said%20they%20were%20unhoused%20when%20the%20payments%20began%2C%20after%20six%20months%20about%2063%25%20of%20them%20said%20they%20had%20found%20housing%2C%20the%20report%20says.%20About%2085%25%20of%20recipients%20reported%20still%20needing%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%20occasional%20assistance%26quot%3B%20with%20getting%20access%20to%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoint%20Source%20Youth%2C%20a%20national%20nonprofit%20focused%20on%20addressing%20the%20problem%20of%20youth%20homelessness%2C%20partnered%20with%20the%20state%20to%20help%20design%2C%20plan%2C%20and%20structure%20the%20program.%20The%20nonprofit%20has%20helped%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguaranteed-universal-basic-income-ubi-baltimore-young-families-success-fund-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20programs%20in%20other%20cities%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20states%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnjala%20Huff%2C%20a%20senior%20director%20at%20the%20organization%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20enrollees%20have%20been%20able%20to%20obtain%20housing%2C%20enroll%20in%20school%2C%20and%20purchase%20cars%20since%20receiving%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program's%20team%20has%20helped%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20participants%20find%20housing.%20The%20goal%20is%20for%20the%20program%20to%20act%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20intervention%26quot%3B%20that%20can%20be%20funded%20with%20public%20money%20in%20the%20future%2C%20Huff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20about%20obtaining%20housing.%20We%20are%20helping%20to%20navigate%20creative%20housing%20conversations%20on%20how%20to%20maintain%20housing%20beyond%20enrollment%20in%20the%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20Huff%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20receiving%20the%20cash%20for%20one%20year%2C%20we%20are%20seeing%20youth%20who%20are%20interested%20i