0to%20stare%20at%20their%20phones%2C%20but%20there%20was%20no%20doubt%20what%20everyone%20was%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20morning%2C%20the%20Russian%20capital%20had%20awoken%20to%20the%20news%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-announces-military-assault-against-ukraine-in-surprise-speech-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVladimir%20Putin%20had%20launched%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20military%20operation%26quot%3B%20in%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20beginning%20what%20was%20to%20become%20the%20largest%20land%20war%20in%20Europe%20since%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20tried%20to%20shrug%20off%20the%20news%20of%20the%20invasion%20with%20an%20apathy%20that%20had%20become%20commonplace%20in%20Putin's%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20colleague%2C%20quite%20confidently%2C%20proclaimed%20that%20%26quot%3Bthis%20thing%20will%20last%20no%20longer%20than%20a%20week.%20Two%20at%20most.%20It's%20not%20a%20big%20deal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20Moscow%20attracted%20a%20very%20particular%20kind%20of%20foreign%20worker%2C%20an%20uncertain%20graduate%20willing%20to%20enjoy%20a%20gap%20year%20making%20money%20at%20not%20especially%20difficult%20jobs%20in%20teaching%2C%20banking%2C%20and%20advertising.%20I%20had%20taken%20up%20just%20such%20a%20job%3A%20I%20as%20a%20private%20tutor%20for%20wealthy%20Russian%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20company's%20office%20was%20on%20Tverskaya%20Street%20in%20central%20Moscow.%20As%20I%20packed%20away%20my%20laptop%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20February%2024%2C%20I%20began%20to%20hear%20chants%20coming%20through%20the%20open%20window.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNyet%20voinye%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3BNo%20to%20war%26quot%3B)%2C%20%26quot%3BPutin%20idi%20nakhui%26quot%3B%20(Fuck%20Putin)%2C%20%26quot%3BPozor%26quot%3B%20(shame)%2C%20%26quot%3BMir%26quot%3B%20(peace).%20The%20cries%20were%20coming%20from%20Pushkin%20Square%20just