3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20several%20Russian%20opposition%20media%20outlets%20were%20shut%20down%20for%20falling%20afoul%20of%20Russia's%20censorship%20of%20coverage%20of%20the%20war%2C%20and%20almost%20all%20Western%20news%20outlets%20suspended%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20the%20war%20entered%20its%20first%20full%20week%2C%20texts%20were%20already%20pinging%20back%20and%20forth%20between%20friends%2C%20foreign%20and%20Russian%2C%20checking%20who%20was%20still%20around%20and%20when%20they%20were%20leaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20began%20to%20research%20the%20merits%20of%20Armenia's%20visa%20policy%20vs%20Turkey's.%20Foreigners%20with%20Russian%20partners%20became%20experts%20on%20Georgia's%20quick%20and%20unbureaucratic%20marriage%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22russians%20leaving%20russia%20armenia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62320f83843ef30018e753d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20and%20Belarus%20people%20as%20they%20wait%20a%20taxi%20at%20the%20airport%20upon%20their%20arrival%20in%20Yerevan%2C%20Armenia%2C%20on%20March%2010%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EKaren%20Minasyan%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%202%2C%20I%20went%20to%20a%20sushi%20restaurant%20for%20lunch%20with%20two%20British%20colleagues.%20One%20was%20incredibly%20anxious.%20The%20other%20had%20pragmatically%20put%20together%20a%20list%20of%20potential%20exit%20routes%20should%20the%20worst%20come%20to%20the%20worst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20waiter%20came%20over%20with%20the%20bill%2C%20our%20Visa%20debit%20cards%20were%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20evening%2C%20well-connected%20friends%20and%20colleagues%20gossiped%20about%20the%20imminent%20imposition%20of%20martial%20law%20and%20the%20closure%20of%20the%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20knew%20we%20had%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Someone%20is%20trying%20to%20kill%20me%2C%20and%20his%20name%20is%20Vladimir%20Putin'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETickets%20to%20Yerevan%2C%20Istanbul%2C%20and%20Dubai%20%E2%80%94%20the%20few%20cities%20still%20open%20to%20Russian%20flights%20%E2%80%94%20were%20selling%20for%20%243%2C000%20apiece.%20Russian%20friends%20began%20referring%20to%20Tbilisi%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bnew%20Constantinople%2C%26quot%3B%20referencing%20the%20city%20where%20anti-Bolshevik%20Russians%20fleeing%20the%20Communist%20revolution%20had%20taken%20refuge%20a%20century%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20settled%20for%20the%20cheapest%20option%3A%20a%20train%20from%20Moscow%20to%20St%20Petersburg%2C%20a%20bus%20from%20St%20Petersburg%20to%20Helsinki%2C%20and%20then%20a%20flight%20home%20to%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Putin%2C%20Macron%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F621cae63101faf00192962d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22632%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20(L)%20meets%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20(R)%20on%20February%2007%2C%202022%20in%20Moscow%2C%20Russia.%3Cp%3EKremlin%20Press%20Office%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20before%20we%20left%20was%20a%20strange%20experience%20where%20a%20concoction%20of%20different%20worlds%20seemed%20to%20merge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20those%20proudly%20walking%20around%20with%20%26quot%3BZ%26quot%3B%20T-shirts%20and%20badges%20as%20signs%20of%20support%20for%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20simply%20apathetic%20to%20Putin's%20invasion.%20Seeing%20people%20going%20to%20the%20theater%20and%20couples%20on%20dinner%20dates%20was%20strange%2C%20as%20though%20nothing%20had%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20subdued%20acceptance%20was%20bizarre%3A%20not%20necessarily%20contentment%2C%20but%20resignation.%20One%20Russian%20colleague%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BLook%20at%20the%20streets.%20Do%20you%20see%20war%3F%20No.%20So%20everything%20is%20fine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Moscow%20Russia%20skyscraper%20drone%20attack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fb812e3d39230019774356%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInvestigators%20examine%20a%20damaged%20skyscraper%20in%20Moscow's%20business%20district%20after%20a%20reported%20drone%20attack%20on%20July%2030%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%2C%20the%20war%20would%20reach%20the%20world%20of%20the%20Moscovite%20as%20Ukraine's%20drones%20struck%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20city%20office%20blocks%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-attacks-russian-energy-infrastructure-small-cheap-drones-2024-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUkraine%2520appears%2520to%2520be%2520attacking%2Ccan%2520bypass%2520its%2520air%2520defenses%26amp%3Btext%3DOil%2520and%2520gas%2520facilities%2520in%2Cregion%2520was%2520ablaze%2520on%2520Saturday.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethen%20oil-and-gas%20targets%20within%20Russian%20territory.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20on%2C%20more%20than%20300%2C000%20Russian%20soldiers%20have%20been%20killed%20or%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20in%20the%20early%20days%2C%20there%20was%20immense%20fear.%20Long%20lines%20of%20people%20formed%20outside%20banks.%20At%20work%2C%20many%20parents%20were%20trying%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20get%20their%20children%20into%20private%20schools%20in%20the%20West.%20Switzerland%20or%20the%20UK%20were%20hot%20choices%20for%20those%20who%20could%20afford%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20mid-March%2C%20some%20300%2C000%20Russians%20had%20left%20the%20country%2C%20and%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20total%20was%20just%20shy%20of%20a%20million.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnumber-of-russians-fleeing-draft-bigger-1st-invasion-force-uk-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt%20was%20a%20mass%20exodus%20of%20Russians%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20saw%20leaving%20as%20the%20only%20means%20of%20protest%20that%20they%20had%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Saint%20Petersburg%20bus%20station%2C%20a%20young%20man%2C%20no%20older%20than%20me%2C%20spoke%20as%20if%20in%20a%20movie%3A%20%26quot%3BSomeone%20in%20this%20country%20is%20trying%20to%20kill%20me%2C%20and%20his%20name%20is%20Vladimir%20Putin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20hope%20to%20be%20back%20soon%2C%20I%20told%20the%20border%20guard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Finish%20boarder%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d879b3ce7f1785b2e35a02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EView%20from%20the%20Finnish%20border%3Cp%3ECameron%20Manley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20border%2C%20they%20took%20people%20into%20rooms%2C%20singling%20out%20the%20conscription-age%20Russian%20men.%20We%20had%20heard%20stories%20of%20interrogations%20lasting%20four%20hours%2C%20with%20phone%20messages%20and%20laptop%20files%20being%20thoroughly%20checked.%20Luckily%2C%20my%20colleagues%20and%20I%20had%20deleted%20WhatsApp%20and%20other%20messaging%20services%20before%20leaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stood%20at%20the%20glass%20window%20silently%20as%20the%20Russian%20border%20guard%20inspected%20my%20passport%20and%20now%20useless%20work%20permit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20to%20be%20back%20soon%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20so%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20border%20guard%20replied%2C%20handing%20me%20back%20my%20passport%20and%20gesturing%20me%20through%20the%20gate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20at%20that%20point%20could%20have%20predicted%20how%20long%2C%20bloody%2C%20brutal%2C%20and%20terrible%20this%20invasion%20would%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20stepped%20into%20Finland%2C%20I%20waved%20goodbye%20to%20Russia%2C%20the%20place%2C%20the%20beautiful%20image%20of%20Russia%2C%20its%20culture%20and%20people%2C%20that%20I%20loved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20I%20continue%20to%20mourn%20that%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoscow-russia-ukraine-war-broke-out%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708775813000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d8abadce7f1785b2e364ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoscow-russia-ukraine-war-broke-out%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cameron%20Manley%20was%20in%20Moscow%20the%20day%20Vladimir%20Putin%20declared%20war%20on%20Ukraine.%20It%20was%20a%20strange%20and%20unnerving%20experience.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cmanley%40businessinsider.com%20(Cameron%20Manley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoscow-russia-ukraine-war-broke-out%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Digital%20nagriks%20not%20to%20be%20experimented%20with%20unreliable%20models%3A%20MoS%20IT%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708775527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F09%2Ffull%2F1691604359-1486.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdon-t-experiment-unreliable-models-with-unreliable-models-govt-to-google-124022400456_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Union%20Minister%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%20on%20Saturday%20made%20it%20clear%20to%20Google%20that%20explanations%20about%20unreliability%20of%20AI%20models%20do%20not%20absolve%20or%20exempt%20platforms%20from%20laws%2C%20and%20warned%20that%20India's%20digital%20'nagriks'%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20to%20be%20experimented%20on%26quot%3B%20with%20...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdon-t-experiment-unreliable-models-with-unreliable-models-govt-to-google-124022400456_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdon-t-experiment-unreliable-models-with-unreliable-models-govt-to-google-124022400456_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fdon-t-experiment-unreliable-models-with-unreliable-models-govt-to-google-124022400456_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20Critic%20May%20Have%20Been%20Killed%20With%20%26quot%3BSingle%20Punch%20To%20Heart%26quot%3B%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussian%20opposition%20leader%20Alexei%20Navalny%20may%20have%20been%20killed%20with%20a%20single%20punch%20to%20the%20heart%20-%20an%20old%20method%20used%20by%20the%20KGB%20-%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20has%20claimed.%20This%20comes%20even%20as%20the%20Russian%20officials%20are%20yet%20to%20release%20Navalny's%20body%20who%20died%20suddenly%20a%20week%20ago%20in%20the%20Arctic%20penal%20colony%20where%20he%20had%20been%20serving%20sentences%20totalling%20more%20than%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20an%20old%20method%20of%20the%20KGB's%20special%20forces%20divisions%2C%26quot%3B%20Vladimir%20Osechkin%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20human%20rights%20group%20Gulagu.net%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Falexei-navalny-killed-punch-death-cause-russia-putin-x86g6jcdx%5C%22%3ETimes%20of%20London%20%3C%2Fa%3Eciting%20a%20source%20at%20the%20penal%20colony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20trained%20their%20operatives%20to%20kill%20a%20man%20with%20one%20punch%20in%20the%20heart%2C%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20body.%20It%20was%20a%20hallmark%20of%20the%20KGB%2C%26quot%3B%20Osechkin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKGB%20was%20much-feared%20Soviet-era%20internal%20security%20service.%20It%20was%20officially%20dissolved%20on%20December%203%2C%201991.%20It%20was%20later%20succeeded%20in%20Russia%20by%20the%20Foreign%20Intelligence%20Service%20(SVR)%20and%20what%20would%20later%20become%20the%20Federal%20Security%20Service%20(FSB).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20ahead%20of%20the%20fatal%20strike%2C%20the%2047-year-old%20had%20been%20kept%20outdoors%20for%20hours%20in%20the%20harsh%2C%20subzero%20temperatures%20to%20weaken%20his%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20they%20first%20destroyed%20his%20body%20by%20keeping%20him%20out%20in%20the%20cold%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20slowing%20the%20blood%20circulation%20down%20to%20a%20minimum%2C%26quot%3B%20Osechkin%20said%2C%20citinig%20an%20unidentified%20source%20working%20at%20the%20prison.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20it%20becomes%20very%20easy%20to%20kill%20someone%2C%20within%20seconds%2C%20if%20the%20operative%20has%20some%20experience%20in%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20report%2C%20the%20body%20of%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20most%20vociferous%20critic%20had%20%26quot%3Bsigns%20of%20bruises%26quot%3B%2C%20an%20anonymours%20paramedic%20told%20an%20independent%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paramedic%20said%20the%20bodies%20of%20those%20who%20die%20in%20prison%20are%20usually%20taken%20straight%20to%20the%20Foreign%20Medicine%20Bureau%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20his%20body%20was%20taken%20to%20a%20clinical%20hospital%20for%20some%20reason.%26quot%3B%20The%20%26quot%3Bbruises%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20body%20resembled%20marks%20that%20one%20suffers%20when%20being%20held%20down%20during%20a%20seizure%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexei%20Navalny's%20team%20has%20claimed%20that%20Russian%20authorities%20have%20told%20his%20mother%20he%20would%20be%20buried%20in%20the%20penal%20colony%20unless%20she%20agreed%20to%20lay%20him%20to%20rest%20without%20a%20public%20funeral.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20mother%20Lyudmila%20has%20been%20demanding%20for%20days%20that%20authorities%20hand%20over%20his%20body%20to%20be%20buried%20in%20a%20way%20that%20will%20allow%20his%20friends%2C%20family%20and%20supporters%20to%20pay%20their%20respects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20family%20and%20supporters%20have%20accused%20Putin%20of%20having%20him%20killed%2C%20an%20accusation%20that%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20angrily%20rejected.%20He%20had%20survived%20a%20poisoning%20attempt%20in%202020%20and%20years%20of%20harsh%20treatment%20in%20prison%2C%20including%20long%20spells%20in%20solitary%20confinement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%2C%20who%20never%20mentioned%20Navalny%20in%20his%20speeches%2C%20has%20not%20yet%20commented%20on%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYulia%20Navalnaya%2C%20the%20widow%20of%20Navalny%2C%20has%20released%20a%20six-minute%20video%20on%20Saturday%20and%20demanded%20that%20Russian%20authorities%20release%20his%20body%20for%20burial%20and%20accused%20a%20%26quot%3Bdemonic%26quot%3B%20Putin%20of%20%26quot%3Btorturing%26quot%3B%20his%20corpse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Russian%20officials%2C%20Navalny%20%26quot%3Bfely%20unwell%20after%20a%20walk%2C%20almost%20immediately%20losing%20consciousness%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BAll%20necessary%20resuscitation%20measures%20were%20carried%20out%2C%20which%20did%20not%20give%20positive%20results.%20Doctors%20of%20the%20ambulance%20stated%20the%20death%20of%20the%20convict.%20The%20causes%20of%20death%20are%20being%20established%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20mother%20was%20given%20a%20notice%20of%20the%20death%20that%20had%202.17%20pm%20local%20time%20(2.37%20pm%20IST)%20on%20February%2016.%20She%20was%20told%20the%20cause%20of%20his%20death%20was%20%26quot%3Bsudden%20death%20syndrome%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSudden%20death%20syndrome%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20vague%20term%20for%20different%20cardiac%20syndromes%20that%20cause%20sudden%20cardiac%20arrest%20and%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708775520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fi21k9img_alexei-navalny_625x300_16_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20opposition%20leader%20Alexei%20Navalny%20may%20have%20been%20killed%20with%20a%20single%20punch%20to%20the%20heart%20-%20an%20old%20method%20used%20by%20the%20KGB%20-%20a%20human%20rights%20activist%20has%20claimed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fputin-critic-alexei-navalny-may-have-been-killed-with-single-punch-to-heart-claims-activist-vladimir-osechkin-5119199%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Criminal%20Laws%2C%20Which%20Replace%20Penal%20Code%2C%20Come%20Into%20Effect%20From%20July%201%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-criminal-laws-passed-in-lok-sabha-with-most-opposition-mps-suspended-4709805%5C%22%3Enew%20criminal%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20come%20into%20effect%20from%20July%201%20and%20replace%20the%20country's%20colonial-era%20legislations%2C%20the%20government%20announced%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20(Second)%20Sanhita%2C%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20