31cb0b764%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221625%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArtificial%20intelligence%20tools%20might%20take%20on%20some%20work%20people%20can't%20find%20the%20time%20to%20get%20to.%3Cp%3Esorbetto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20workers%20are%20worried%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-boom-nvidia-1995-moment-analyst-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20come%20for%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYet%20AI%20might%20sometimes%20be%20more%20like%C2%A0an%20intern%20%E2%80%94%20taking%20on%20tasks%20that%20otherwise%20wouldn't%20get%20done.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20AI%20tools%20can%20also%20help%20in%20fields%20like%20accounting%20where%20there's%20a%20shortage%20of%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20most%20people%2C%20there%20were%20things%20on%20Heather%20Holding's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Flearning%2Fbest-planner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto-do%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20knew%20she'd%20never%20get%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20led%20Holding%2C%20who%20oversees%20risk%20management%20at%20fintech%20company%20Best%20Egg%2C%20to%20wonder%20whether%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20tool%20could%20draft%20policy%20documents%20she%20and%20her%20colleagues%20couldn't%20find%20time%20to%20pull%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20day%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'You%20know%20what%2C%20let's%20just%20try%20to%20put%20these%20through%2C'%26quot%3B%20Holding%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20So%2C%20she%20wrote%20prompts%20for%20an%20AI%20tool%20built%20into%20a%20corporate%20reporting%20platform%20made%20by%20Workiva.%20The%20chatbot%20drafted%20documents%20that%20needed%20some%20tweaking%2C%20but%20Holding%20and%20her%20team%20got%20through%20the%20backlog%20of%2010%20policies%20within%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20operate%20very%20lean.%20So%20something%20like%20this%20is%20really%20a%20game%20changer%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHolding's%20experience%20points%20to%20the%20sometimes%20subtle%20ways%20AI%20is%20changing%20work.%20Many%20workers%20have%20expressed%20fears%20that%20the%20technology%20will%20show%20up%20at%20the%20office%20like%20a%20young%20gun%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-jobs-at-risk-replacement-artificial-intelligence-ai-labor-trends-2023-02%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoming%20for%20their%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20AI%20might%20be%20more%20like%20the%20temp%20that%20gets%20brought%20in%20when%20work%20piles%20up%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20to%20do%20the%20jobs%20nobody%20wanted%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20AI%20bot%20could%20act%20as%20your%20intern.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20chatbots%20like%20the%20one%20Holding%20used%20might%20not%20take%20over%20tons%20of%20jobs%20right%20away%20is%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftransformers-limits-chatgpt-researchers-examining-alternative-ai-models-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elimits%20to%20what%20AI%20can%20do%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20for%20now.%20Generative%20AI%20tools%20often%20still%20require%20oversight%2C%20much%20like%20an%20inexperienced%20worker%20might.%20Holding%20has%20to%20review%20and%20sometimes%20adjust%20what%20a%20bot%20kicks%20out%2C%20but%20even%20with%20that%2C%20she%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaves%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20write%20a%20policy%20doc%20from%20scratch%2C%20she%20said%2C%20might%20take%20from%20eight%20to%2030%20hours%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20type%20and%20how%20much%20research%20it%20requires.%20As%20long%20as%20she%20does%20the%20upfront%20legwork%20to%20draft%20the%20proper%20instructions%20for%20the%20bot%2C%20the%20results%20are%20compelling%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20literally%20have%20the%20sections%20mirror%20exactly%20what%20you%20want%20in%20an%20actual%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20Holding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETackling%20those%20jobs%20that%20people%20otherwise%20might%20not%20even%20start%20is%20an%20important%20part%20of%20how%20AI%20will%20transform%20the%20workplace%2C%20according%20to%20Ron%20Williams%2C%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Kindo%2C%20which%20helps%20companies%20adopt%20and%20use%20AI%20tools%20securely.%20In%20part%2C%20it's%20because%20the%20technology%20lets%20companies%20do%20things%20they%20couldn't%20do%20easily%20or%20cost-effectively%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20jobs%20not%20getting%20done%20today%20that%20aren't%20threatened%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20AI%20is%20just%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20start%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20expects%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20gains%20from%20AI%20won't%20center%20on%20what%20companies%20and%20workers%20are%20doing%20now.%20Instead%2C%20he%20sees%20major%20wins%20coming%20from%20what%20workers%20aren't%20doing%20but%20that%20AI%20could.%20Accomplishing%20those%20things%20could%20change%20the%20trajectory%20of%20a%20business%2C%20Williams%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20AIs%20get%20better%2C%20that's%20just%20going%20to%20accelerate%20and%20expand%20the%20reach%20of%20what%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20pointed%20to%20work%20such%20as%20content%20moderation%20or%20aggregating%20reviews%20in%20e-commerce.%20He%20said%20AI%20can%20sift%20through%20thousands%20of%20posts%20and%20summarize%20customers'%20sentiments%20about%20a%20product.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-testing-artificial-intelligence-ai-generated-product-review-feature-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20is%20trying%20this%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hot%20takes%20from%20AI%20could%20boost%20sales%2C%20Williams%20said%2C%20if%20shoppers%20have%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20what%20people%20think%20about%20a%20product.%20It's%20the%20kind%20of%20service%20that%20wasn't%20feasible%20without%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%2C%20that%20just%20wasn't%20economical%20to%20have%20a%20human%20go%20through%20and%20try%20to%20aggregate%20that%20stuff%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFilling%20in%20when%20help%20is%20scarce%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20jobs%20sometimes%20aren't%20getting%20done%20is%20because%20there%20aren't%20always%20enough%20workers.%20So%2C%20some%20leaders%20are%20looking%20to%20AI%20for%20help.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FGigged.AI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGigged.AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20of%20about%20250%20UK%20execs%20in%20mid-2023%2C%20about%20half%20said%20GenAI%20could%20address%20skills%20shortages%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20also%20efforts%20to%20train%20workers%20in%20fields%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshortage-accountants-we-should-be-worried-recruit-young-talent-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccounting%20that%20are%20facing%20worker%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20about%20the%20benefits%20of%20AI.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EA%20startup%20called%20Docyt%20recently%20introduced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocyt.com%2Funiversity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional%20development%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20teach%20accountants%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20complete%20their%20jobs%20more%20efficiently%20and%20accurately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJ%C3%A9r%C3%B4me%20Pesenti%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20an%20AI-powered%20learning%20app%20called%20Sizzle%20and%20former%20VP%20of%20AI%20at%20Facebook%20parent%20Meta%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20sometimes%20AI%20takes%20on%20parts%20of%20jobs%20that%20might%20be%20unexpected.%20He%20pointed%20to%20research%20labs%20where%20machines%20excel%20at%20repeating%20experiments%20with%20high%20precision.%20But%20tasks%20that%20might%20seem%20menial%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0like%20cleaning%20machines%20and%20moving%20samples%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0are%20actually%20often%20harder%20to%20leave%20to%20robots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20literally%20decades%20away%20from%20automating%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYet%20some%20jobs%20that%20we%20thought%20were%2C%20you%20know%2C%20maybe%20like%20higher%20level%2C%20which%20was%20like%20doing%20precise%20experiments%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it%20actually%20turns%20out%20machines%20are%20better%20at%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHumans%20still%20come%20out%20ahead%20in%20areas%20like%20behaving%20in%20a%20complex%20environment%20and%20dealing%20with%20multiple%20systems%2C%20Pesenti%20said.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20people%20won't%20turn%20to%20AI%20as%20a%20hired%20hand%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20he%20noted.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20still%20betting%20on%20the%20human%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20the%20human%20needs%20to%20leverage%20the%20machine%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Pesenti%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestegg.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBest%20Egg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Holding%20hopes%20AI%20might%20one%20day%20take%20on%20even%20more%20work%2C%20like%20scooping%20up%20thousands%20of%20rows%20of%20data%20and%20allowing%20auditors%20to%20ask%20a%20chatbot%20questions%20about%20that%20information%20or%20hunt%20down%20anomalies.%20Right%20now%2C%20she%20might%20spend%20up%20to%2040%20hours%20conducting%20transactional%20tests.%20If%20AI%20could%20be%20deployed%20to%20help%20with%20this%20work%2C%20the%20time%20the%20task%20takes%20might%20get%20cut%20in%20half%2C%20Holding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20all%20kind%20of%20leaning%20into%20this%20technology%20to%20help%20us%20do%20more%20with%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D