ration.%20Rising%20from%20below%2C%20Tantra%20fused%20with%20Jainism%2C%20Buddhism%2C%20the%20Puranic%20sects%20of%20Shaiva%2C%20Vaishnava%2C%20and%20Shakta%2C%20and%20inspired%20sexual%20imagery%20on%20their%20monuments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sex-positive%2C%20anti-caste%2C%20and%20goddess-centric%20folk%20culture%20of%20Tantra%20was%20also%20the%20soil%20that%20sustained%20the%20secular%20hedonism%20of%20the%20elites%20and%20the%20Kamasutra.%20But%20then%20came%20a%20huge%20conservative%20blowback%20within%20Hinduism%20that%20decimated%20Tantra.%20Discover%20the%20lost%20world%20of%20Khajuraho%2C%20the%20influence%20of%20Tantrism%20in%20early%20medieval%20India%2C%20and%20its%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FLiM8QS2gWn0%3Fsi%3DCD1MEPBr-BdN3iEG%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20the%20transcription%20of%20the%20entire%20episode.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20Indians.%20I%E2%80%99m%20Namit%20Arora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%20episode%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20Nalanda%2C%20the%20accounts%20of%20three%20Chinese%20travellers%2C%20and%20the%20decline%20of%20Buddhism%20in%20India%20during%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20first%20millennium.%20This%20was%20a%20time%20of%20great%20social%20and%20religious%20churning.%20Today%20I%E2%80%99ll%20look%20at%20how%20this%20played%20out%20at%20Khajuraho%2C%20a%20site%20now%20famous%20for%20its%20amazingly%20beautiful%20temples%20that%20also%20show%20graphic%20sex%20on%20their%20walls.%20Such%20temples%20were%20built%20across%20India.%20Who%20built%20them%2C%20and%20what%20were%20they%20thinking%3F%20What%20led%20them%20to%20combine%20religious%20moods%20with%20sex%3F%20And%20why%20do%20modern%20Hindus%20and%20their%20temples%20lack%20this%20worldview%20entirely%3F%20I%20mean%2C%20what%20happened%20to%20us%3F%E2%80%94how%20did%20we%20go%20from%20there%20to%20this%20country%20of%20prudes!%20I%E2%80%99ll%20tackle%20all%20that%E2%80%94and%20more%E2%80%94in%20this%20episode.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Discovery%20of%20Khajuraho%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhajuraho%20was%20the%20capital%20of%20the%20Chandela%20kingdom%20(c.%20831%E2%80%931315)%2C%20where%20the%20Chandelas%20built%2085%20temples%2C%20mostly%20between%20900%E2%80%931150.%20Twenty-five%20of%20these%20temples%20have%20survived.%20They%20had%20been%20buried%20in%20a%20forest%20for%20centuries%20until%20their%20rediscovery%20in%201838%20by%20a%20British%20engineer%2C%20who%20was%20scandalised%20by%20the%20sexual%20imagery.%20He%20called%20the%20sculptures%20%E2%80%98indecent%20and%20offensive%E2%80%99%20and%20wondered%20how%20any%20chaste%20religion%20could%20permit%20such%20depictions.%20Alexander%20Cunningham%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20in%201861%2C%20called%20them%20%E2%80%98disgustingly%20obscene%E2%80%99.%20Clearly%2C%20these%20were%20men%20of%20the%20Victorian%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20temples%20feature%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20sexual%20scenes%2C%20which%20make%20up%20less%20than%20ten%20percent%20of%20their%20sculptures.%20They%20also%20show%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20major%20and%20minor%20gods.%20Secular%20subject%20matter%20abounds%2C%20including%20young%20maidens%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20moods%20and%20activities%2C%20teachers%20and%20disciples%2C%20dancers%20and%20musicians%2C%20royal%20hunts%2C%20marching%20armies%2C%20battle%20scenes%2C%20animals%20like%20elephants%2C%20parrots%2C%20snakes%2C%20and%20much%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Enigma%20of%20Erotic%20Art%20on%20Temples%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20erotica%20that%E2%80%99s%20most%20puzzling.%20What%20sort%20of%20a%20worldview%20puts%20hardcore%20sex%20next%20to%20their%20gods%3F%20It%20challenges%20our%20thinking%20about%20religious%20art%20and%20%E2%80%98proper%E2%80%99%20spiritual%20moods%20and%20sentiments.%20These%20temples%20depict%20not%20just%20heterosexual%20coitus%20but%20also%20masturbation%2C%20orgies%2C%20oral%20sex%2C%20lesbian%20and%20gay%20sex%2C%20exhibitionism%2C%20and%20even%20bestiality.%20The%20panels%20depict%20youthful%20men%20and%20women%20with%20idealised%20bodies%2C%20but%20also%20bearded%2C%20rudraksha-wearing%2C%20pot-bellied%20ascetics%2C%20acharyas%2C%20and%20yogis%20having%20sex%E2%80%94a%20far%20cry%20from%20today%E2%80%99s%20idea%20of%20these%20roles.%20In%20fact%2C%20modern%20Hindu%20temples%20do%20not%20show%20any%20sex%20at%20all.%20So%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20on%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20Khajuraho%20was%20not%20unusual%20for%20its%20time.%20Many%20medieval%20temples%20across%20India%20carried%20such%20depictions%20on%20their%20walls%20and%20even%20in%20their%20inner%20sanctums%E2%80%94at%20Badami%2C%20Bhubaneshwar%2C%20Konark.%20How%20did%20a%20religious%20culture%20that%20had%20long%20glorified%20austerity%2C%20renunciation%2C%20and%20asceticism%20as%20the%20path%20to%20God%2C%20approve%20of%20such%20sexual%20imagery%E2%80%94on%20temples%2C%20no%20less!%20Most%20Indians%20today%20are%20so%20prudish%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20scandalised%20by%20this%20imagery%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%20alien%20to%20them.%20I%20mean%2C%20kissing%20scenes%20came%20into%20Bollywood%20barely%20a%20generation%20ago%2C%20and%20we%20still%20can%E2%80%99t%20watch%20them%20with%20our%20parents%20in%20the%20same%20room.%20So%20what%20motivated%20our%20medieval%20ancestors%20to%20create%20this%3F%20What%20was%20its%20meaning%20back%20then%3F%20And%20why%20did%20it%20disappear%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20Temple%20Art%20Inspired%20by%20the%20Kamasutra%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20say%2C%20oh%2C%20it%20was%20a%20liberal%20age%2C%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Kamasutra%2C%20when%20Indians%20had%20few%20sexual%20hang-ups.%20The%20sculptures%2C%20they%20say%2C%20are%20a%20visual%20illustration%20of%20the%20Kamasutra%2C%20and%20were%20commissioned%20by%20libertine%20aristocrats.%20But%20this%20is%20a%20lazy%20answer%2C%20and%20it%20collapses%20if%20we%20think%20about%20it%20carefully.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kamasutra%20is%20not%20a%20religious%20or%20spiritual%20text.%20It%20is%20about%20the%20earthly%20art%20of%20love%20and%20courtship.%20Its%20audience%20was%20the%20urban%20upper%20crust%20who%20pursued%20erotic%20pleasure%20as%20an%20end%20in%20itself.%20It%20dates%20from%20the%20early%20first%20millennium%2C%20near%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%20Gupta%20Empire.%20Though%20attributed%20to%20Vatsyayana%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20a%20composite%20work%20that%20had%20evolved%20over%20centuries.%20Back%20then%2C%20many%20other%20texts%20advised%20people%20on%20sexual%20love%2C%20courtship%20and%20even%20adultery.%20The%20Kamasutra%20is%20only%20the%20best%20known%20of%20them.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20patriarchal%20text%2C%20and%20the%20modern%20reader%20will%20find%20in%20it%20plenty%20of%20regressive%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Kamasutra%20can%20also%20be%20surprisingly%20progressive.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20sees%20women%20as%20full%20participants%20in%20sexual%20life%2C%20as%20individuals%20gladly%20engaging%20in%20an%20exciting%20social%20game.%20It%20is%20attentive%20to%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20feelings%20and%20emotions%20that%20a%20man%20should%20understand%20to%20increase%20erotic%20pleasure.%20It%20stresses%20the%20importance%20of%20grooming%2C%20etiquette%2C%20diplomacy%2C%20and%20post-coital%20conversation.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20a%20manual%20for%20men%3B%20it%20also%20offers%20advice%20to%20maidens%2C%20courtesans%2C%20wives%2C%20and%20mistresses.%20It%20advocates%20marriages%20based%20on%20love%20over%20arranged%20ones%2C%20and%20it%20discusses%20practical%20matters%20like%20how%20to%20find%20a%20partner%20and%20maintain%20power%20in%20a%20marriage.%20It%20does%20catalogue%20a%20range%20of%20sexual%20positions%E2%80%94some%20impossibly%20athletic%20ones!%E2%80%94but%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20a%20treatise%20on%20the%20art%20of%20intimate%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20secular%20treatise%2C%20the%20Kamasutra%20can%20at%20best%20explain%20erotic%20imagery%20in%20private%20spaces%2C%20on%20personal%20objects%20like%20combs%2C%20paintings%2C%20or%20ivory%20panels.%20It%20does%20not%20explain%20why%20it%20was%20alright%20to%20put%20graphic%20sex%20on%20temple%20walls%2C%20next%20to%20the%20gods.%20Why%20would%20the%20royals%20put%20erotica%20on%20state%20temples%20and%20risk%20offending%20their%20subjects%3F%20So%20what%20explains%20these%20depictions%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Tantric%20Substrate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20first%20have%20to%20remember%20that%20religious%20culture%20back%20then%20was%20very%20different%20from%20ours%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it%20seems%20alien%20and%20scandalous%20to%20modern%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20difference%20was%20Tantra%E2%80%94a%20religious%20worldview%20whose%20pre-historic%20roots%20lie%20outside%20the%20Vedic%20and%20Buddhist%20fold.%20Tantra%20comes%20from%20non-Aryan%20folk%20traditions%2C%20in%20which%20people%20revered%20the%20idea%20of%20fertility%20and%20had%20built%20magico-religious%20practices%20around%20it.%20Their%20symbols%20of%20fertility%20evoked%20male-female%20unions.%20The%20yoni-lingam%20is%20one%20example.%20Some%20symbols%20were%20abstract%2C%20others%20were%20more%20concrete.%20They%20appeared%20on%20private%20votive%20offerings%20to%20fertility%20goddesses.%20A%20young%20couple%20aspiring%20for%20a%20child%20might%20offer%20such%20terracotta%20plaques%20to%20a%20goddess%20like%20Sri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20Mauryan%20era%2C%20the%20images%20on%20these%20plaques%20became%20more%20literal.%20They%20showed%20amorous%20couples%E2%80%94some%20even%20in%20the%20act%20of%20mating.%20Depictions%20of%20fertility%20goddesses%2C%20including%20the%20lotus-headed%20Lajja%20Gauri%2C%20also%20became%20popular%20on%20discrete%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20time%2C%20these%20symbols%20of%20fertility%20started%20migrating%20from%20small%2C%20private%20objects%20to%20the%20public%20sites%20of%20dominant%20religions.%20The%20earliest%20such%20fusion%20of%20sexual%20and%20religious%20imagery%20that%20we%20know%20of%2C%20appeared%20on%20the%20stupas%20of%20Sanchi%20and%20Bharhut.%20But%20these%20early%20depictions%20on%20large%20monuments%20were%20still%20tame%20and%20mainly%20showed%20voluptuous%20yakshis%2C%20who%20were%20associated%20with%20fertility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20safe%20to%20say%20that%20the%20inspiration%20for%20this%20religious%20fusion%20came%20not%20from%20the%20Buddha%2C%20but%20from%20the%20syncretic%20milieu%20of%20the%20common%20people%20who%20built%20such%20monuments.%20They%20liked%20the%20Buddha%E2%80%99s%20message%2C%20but%20they%20also%20revered%20their%20traditional%20fertility%20cults%20and%20symbols.%20Placing%20them%20on%20Buddhist%20sites%20made%20Buddhism%20even%20more%20appealing%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20first%20millennium%2C%20Tantrism%20evolved%20into%20a%20complex%20set%20of%20beliefs%20and%20meditative%20practices.%20It%20was%20a%20non-dualistic%20system%20that%20embraced%20the%20whole%20human%20being%E2%80%94mind%20and%20body%E2%80%94in%20spiritual%20practice.%20This%20made%20it%20very%20different%20from%20Brahminism%2C%20Buddhism%2C%20and%20Jainism%2C%20because%20central%20to%20these%20three%20was%20the%20idea%20that%20worldly%20temptations%2C%20cravings%2C%20and%20physical%20desires%20are%20impediments%20to%20spiritual%20growth%20and%20liberation.%20They%20idealised%20asceticism%20and%20renunciation.%20But%20Tantrism%20took%20the%20opposite%20view.%20It%20valued%20worldly%20success%20and%20held%20that%20spirituality%20was%20intertwined%20with%20success%20in%20love.%20In%20Tantrism%2C%20properly%20guided%20sexual%20love%20was%20a%20path%20to%20spiritual%20progress%20and%20eventual%20liberation%2C%20or%20moksha.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20sexuality%20was%20a%20path%20to%20the%20divine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Rise%20of%20Erotica%20on%20Religious%20Monuments%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Tantrism%20that%20furnished%20a%20worldview%20in%20which%20sex%20and%20religion%20were%20unified%20pursuits.%20It%20rose%20from%20below%20and%20fused%20with%20popular%20Puranic%20sects%20of%20Shaiva%2C%20Vaishnava%2C%20Shakta%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Buddhism%20and%20Jainism.%20To%20varying%20extents%2C%20Tantric%20sexual%20and%20yogic%20practices%20became%20common%20in%20religious%20life%20after%20the%20mid-first%20millennium.%20The%20goal%20of%20such%20practices%20was%20not%20hedonism%20but%20a%20higher%20state%20of%20awakening.%20Many%20upper-class%20folks%20also%20embraced%20this%20sex-positive%20religiosity%2C%20which%20then%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20sexual%20art%20on%20monumental%20religious%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20centuries%20of%20the%20Common%20Era%2C%20partly%20influenced%20by%20Greco-Gandharan%20art%2C%20greater%20realism%20and%20sensualism%20appeared%20in%20monumental%20stone%20art%20in%20India.%20As%20with%20the%20private%20votive%20objects%20earlier%2C%20the%20fertility%20theme%20on%20temple%20walls%20was%20initially%20evoked%20using%20couples%20holding%20hands%20or%20embracing.%20Such%20amorous%20pairs%20soon%20became%20an%20auspicious%20and%20decorative%20motif%2C%20or%20alankara%2C%20on%20the%20monuments%20of%20all%20major%20religions.%20They%20appeared%20on%20temples%20across%20India%2C%20in%20Mathura%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Mysore%2C%20Ajanta%2C%20Ellora%2C%20Badami%2C%20Aihole%2C%20Pattadakal%2C%20and%20Bhubaneshwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20time%2C%20these%20public%20depictions%20grew%20more%20graphic%2C%20as%20they%20had%20done%20earlier%20on%20private%20votive%20offerings.%20The%20earliest%20sculptures%20with%20couples%20having%20sex%20appeared%20on%20religious%20monuments%20in%20the%20mid-first%20millennium%20CE.%20They%20were%20initially%20small%20and%20discreetly%20placed.%20But%20the%20size%2C%20finesse%2C%20and%20centrality%20of%20erotic%20art%20on%20temples%20kept%20growing%20until%20it%20became%20an%20artistic%20convention.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20this%20paralleled%20the%20rise%20of%20Tantrism%2C%20which%20had%20infiltrated%20all%20major%20religious%20sects%20like%20Shaiva%2C%20Vaishnava%2C%20Shakta%2C%20Buddhist%2C%20and%20Jain.%20And%20it%20had%20infused%20in%20them%20its%20spiritual%20concepts%20for%20mixing%20sexuality%20with%20divinity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20note%20that%20these%20depictions%20did%20not%20shock%20or%20scandalise%20the%20public%20because%20they%20had%20come%20from%20grassroots%20beliefs%20and%20the%20familiar%20imagery%20of%20votive%20offerings.%20The%20public%20would%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20in%20these%20temple%20sculptures%20a%20sense%20of%20beauty%2C%20divine%20order%2C%20auspiciousness%2C%20fertility%2C%20and%20prosperity.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20sensual%20images%20were%20meant%20to%20comfort%E2%80%94not%20offend%20or%20challenge%E2%80%94the%20sensibilities%20of%20the%20temple-goer.%20The%20royals%20who%20sponsored%20such%20sculptures%20on%20religious%20sites%20hoped%20mainly%20to%20convey%20a%20stable%2C%20harmonious%20vision%20of%20life%E2%80%94and%20to%20acquire%20merit%2C%20fame%2C%20and%20legitimacy%20for%20their%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKhajuraho%E2%80%99s%20Religious%20Landscape%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Chandela%20realm%2C%20there%20was%20virtually%20no%20Buddhism%2C%20which%20had%20already%20receded%20to%20a%20few%20pockets%20in%20eastern%20and%20southern%20India.%20Khajuraho%20had%20a%20mix%20of%20Tantric-Puranic%20faiths%20that%20had%20also%20absorbed%20many%20Brahminical%20ideas%E2%80%94its%20rituals%2C%20texts%2C%20caste%20rules%2C%20Advaita%20thought.%20Scholars%20would%20later%20call%20this%20religious%20soup%20%E2%80%98Hinduism%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20this%2C%20shall%20we%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Original%E2%80%99%20Hinduism%2C%20plus%20some%20Jainism%2C%20that%20made%20up%20the%20religious%20landscape%20of%20Khajuraho.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20subscribers%20of%20this%20%E2%80%98Original%E2%80%99%20Hinduism%2C%20depicting%20sexual%20couplings%20next%20to%20Puranic%20deities%20was%20a%20perfectly%20harmonious%20thing%20to%20do.%20That%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20what%20the%20Chandela%20royals%20commissioned%20on%20state-sponsored%20temples.%20And%20once%20it%20began%2C%20other%20mundane%20factors%20drove%20more%20sex%20on%20their%20walls.%20Temples%20competed%20for%20visitors%2C%20prestige%2C%20and%20donations%2C%20so%20they%20stood%20to%20gain%20by%20literally%20amping%20up%20their%20sex%20appeal.%20A%20Shilpa%20Shastra%20text%20of%20the%20day%2C%20a%20canon%20of%20architecture%2C%20saw%20religion%20as%20partly%20entertainment%20and%20mentioned%20the%20use%20of%20erotic%20temple%20art%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98delight%20of%20the%20people%E2%80%99.%20More%20kinds%20of%20erotica%20made%20temples%20more%20amusing%20and%20popular.%20In%20time%2C%20a%20competitively%20playful%20dynamic%20took%20hold%2C%20and%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20sexual%20scenes%20appeared%20on%20temple%20walls%2C%20including%20some%20that%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20fertility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Erotic%20Lives%20of%20the%20Rich%20%26amp%3B%20Famous%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tantric%20folk%20substrate%20of%20early%20medieval%20India%20was%20immensely%20sex-positive.%20It%20was%20also%20the%20soil%20in%20which%20the%20secular%20hedonism%20of%20the%20aristocrats%20thrived.%20This%20was%20especially%20true%20of%20the%20Chandelas%2C%20who%20probably%20had%20a%20natural%20affinity%20to%20Tantric%20ideas%20and%20symbols%2C%20since%20they%20came%20from%20lower%20social%20ranks%20with%20tribal%20associations.%20They%20were%20an%20upwardly%20mobile%20group%20who%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Brahmins%2C%20had%20successfully%20invented%20and%20legitimised%20a%20Kshatriya%20genealogy%20that%20made%20them%20Rajputs%20of%20the%20lunar%20line%2C%20or%20Chandravanshis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chandelas%20and%20other%20%E2%80%98Kamasutra%20elites%E2%80%99%20pursued%20erotic%20pleasure%20as%20a%20secular%20end%20in%20itself.%20In%20theory%2C%20Tantric%20sexual%20practices%20had%20higher%20spiritual%20ends%20but%20many%20pleasure-loving%20aristocrats%E2%80%94and%20their%20obliging%20gurus%E2%80%94reduced%20it%20to%20mere%20hedonism.%20Wealthy%20men%20sought%20the%20company%20of%20courtesans%2C%20who%20were%20educated%2C%20cultured%2C%20upper-class%20women%20proficient%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98sixty-four%20arts%E2%80%99%20of%20refinement%2C%20like%20music%2C%20dance%2C%20and%20the%20art%20of%20love.%20Though%20roundly%20condemned%20by%20orthodox%20Brahmins%2C%20these%20courtesans%20lived%20in%20posh%20areas%20of%20the%20city%2C%20could%20choose%20their%20clients%2C%20and%20were%20often%20seen%20as%20celebrities.%20Many%20kings%20and%20aristocrats%20kept%20concubines%20and%20took%20them%20on%20hunting%20trips%2C%20picnics%2C%20water-sports%2C%20summer%20resorts%2C%20and%20even%20battles.%20Prostitution%20was%20both%20legal%20and%20taxed.%20The%20state%20punished%20rapists%2C%20which%20might%20include%20physically%20branding%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20aristocratic%20men%2C%20a%20highly%20coveted%20life%20experience%20was%20an%20extramarital%20affair%20with%20a%20married%20woman.%20Their%20wives%20also%20had%20affairs.%20In%20royal%20parties%2C%20women%20and%20men%20consumed%20alcohol%20in%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20company%20and%20mingled%20freely.%20In%20official%20eulogies%20and%20inscriptions%2C%20kings%20were%20described%20as%20great%20lovers.%20They%20kept%20harems%20with%20women%20from%20all%20over%20India%20and%20even%20Africa%20and%20Arabia.%20Sanskrit%20poets%20and%20erotica%20writers%20of%20the%20day%20delighted%20in%20describing%20the%20sexual%20charms%20of%20women%20from%20different%20regions.%20Aphrodisiacs%20and%20sex%20potions%20were%20much%20in%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20medieval%20temples%20recruited%20devadasis%2C%20or%20young%20women%20who%20learned%20dancing%2C%20singing%2C%20music%20and%20theatre%2C%20which%20they%20performed%20publicly%20at%20the%20temples.%20They%20pioneered%20and%20innovated%20many%20forms%20of%20art%2C%20such%20as%20the%20dance%20form%20Sadir%2C%20a%20precursor%20to%20Bharatanatyam.%20Many%20devadasis%20earned%20wealth%20and%20fame%2C%20but%20many%20also%20served%20as%20prostitutes%20to%20temple%20priests%2C%20pilgrims%2C%20state%20officials%2C%20and%20the%20royals.%20Clearly%2C%20worshipping%20gods%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20always%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20folks%20associated%20with%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20common%20people%20too%20had%20fewer%20hang-ups%20about%20sex%20and%20courtship%20when%20compared%20to%20their%20counterparts%20today.%20During%20certain%20revelries%20and%20festivals%20of%20fertility%E2%80%94amid%20alcohol%2C%20song%2C%20and%20dance%E2%80%94a%20wider%20cross-section%20of%20the%20public%20let%20their%20hair%20down%20and%20ignored%20conventional%20restraints%20on%20sexual%20morality%E2%80%94of%20caste%20and%20class%2C%20for%20instance.%20Married%20men%20and%20women%20were%20said%20to%20pursue%20one-night%20stands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Brahminical%20Backlash%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnTantrism%20itself%20had%20many%20sects%20with%20differing%20beliefs%20and%20practices.%20Most%20were%20mild%20or%20moderate%20and%20were%20socially%20integrated.%20Some%20Tantric%20gurus%20even%20advised%20kings%20on%20their%20sex%20lives%20and%20held%20high%20positions%20in%20temple%20organisations.%20An%20extreme%20sect%20of%20Tantrics%20was%20the%20Shaiva%20Kapalika%2C%20from%20whom%20today%E2%80%99s%20Aghori%20babas%20come.%20Its%20members%20led%20aloof%20and%20solitary%20lives%2C%20and%20took%20delight%20in%20transgressive%20acts%20and%20breaking%20taboos.%20They%20hated%20Brahmins%20and%20often%20used%20a%20Brahmin%E2%80%99s%20empty%20skull%20as%20an%20eating%20or%20begging%20bowl.%20No%20wonder%20the%20Brahmins%20hated%20them%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20sat%20well%20with%20orthodox%20Brahminism%2C%20which%20had%20long%20had%20a%20strain%20of%20sexual%20prudery.%20The%20sexual%20mores%20of%20the%20Tantric%20substrate%20troubled%20the%20Brahmins.%20The%20Tantric%20path%20of%20achieving%20liberation%20through%20ritualised%20sex%20clashed%20directly%20with%20the%20austere%20path%20advocated%20by%20the%20Vedas.%20Tantra%20venerated%20goddesses%20that%20were%20often%20fierce%2C%20powerful%2C%20and%20independent%20of%20male%20gods.%20It%20accorded%20higher%20dignity%20to%20women%2C%20who%20could%20also%20perform%20its%20sacred%20rituals.%20Tantra%20welcomed%20all%20castes%2C%20condemned%20practices%20like%20the%20caste%20system%20and%20sati%2C%20and%20disregarded%20notions%20of%20ritual%20purity%20and%20pollution.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20Tantrism%20clashed%20with%20Brahminical%20conservatism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Decline%20of%20Tantrism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20conflicts%20are%20partly%20why%20the%20Tantric%20substrate%20almost%20died%20out%20in%20much%20of%20India.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20fascinating%20story%20with%20two%20major%20developments.%20First%20was%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Bhakti%20Movement%20in%20south%20India%20that%20preached%20mystical%20love%2C%20devotion%2C%20and%20surrender%20to%20a%20personal%20god.%20It%20was%20an%20outgrowth%20of%20folk%20religiosity%20that%20looked%20down%20on%20worldly%20pleasures.%20Its%20folk%20origins%20meant%20that%20it%20shared%20many%20anti-Brahminical%20and%20gender-egalitarian%20instincts%20with%20Tantra%2C%20but%20not%20its%20sex-positive%20spirituality.%20Instead%2C%20the%20Bhakti%20Movement%20held%20devotion%20as%20the%20path%20to%20the%20divine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%20was%20a%20revival%20of%20Brahminical%20orthodoxy%20by%20the%20influential%20theologian%2C%20Adi%20Shankara%20(est.%20late%208th%20cent.)%2C%20a%20Namboodri%20Brahmin%20whose%20ancestry%20was%20north%20Indian.%20A%20staunch%20conservative%20and%20a%20proponent%20of%20Advaita%20Vedanta%2C%20his%20key%20innovation%20was%20to%20cleverly%20appropriate%20all%20Puranic%20cults%20under%20Brahminism%20by%20declaring%20gods%20like%20Vishnu%2C%20Shiva%2C%20Shakti%2C%20Ganesh%2C%20and%20Surya%20as%20forms%20of%20the%20one%20and%20only%20Supreme%20Being.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20he%20created%20a%20framework%20in%20which%20various%20Puranic%20cults%20and%20devotional%20practices%20got%20subsumed%20under%20the%20Brahminical%20cosmology%20of%20a%20Unitary%20Godhead%2C%20or%20Brahman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdi%20Shankara%E2%80%99s%20Brahminical%20revivalism%20and%20the%20Bhakti%20Movement%20greatly%20increased%20the%20ranks%20of%20the%20orthodox%20and%20the%20prudes.%20They%20first%20squeezed%20out%20Buddhism%20and%20then%20the%20sex-positive%20Tantric%20religiosity.%20This%20was%20a%20huge%20setback%20for%20intellectual%20culture%20and%20creativity%20in%20India.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20first%20millennium%2C%20Indian%20society%20was%20well%20on%20its%20way%20to%20becoming%20more%20conservative%2C%20devotional%2C%20puritanical%2C%20hierarchical%2C%20and%20patriarchal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20caused%20this%20decline%20were%20fault-lines%20and%20conflicts%20within%20Indian%20religious%20culture.%20We%20can%20see%20this%20in%20the%20literature%20of%20the%20period%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Chandela%20court%20play%2C%20Prabodha%20Chandrodaya%20(or%20%E2%80%98moon%20rise%20of%20true%20knowledge%E2%80%99).%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20allegory%20written%20by%20Krishna%20Mishra%20and%20was%20staged%20in%201065.%20In%20this%20play%2C%20Brahminical%20forces%20unite%20and%20rail%20against%20the%20non-Vedic%20forces%20of%20Tantrism%2C%20Buddhism%2C%20Jainism%2C%20and%20the%20Carvakas.%20Such%20views%20were%20gaining%20ground%20not%20only%20in%20the%20Chandela%20court%2C%20but%20across%20most%20Indian%20dynasties%20in%20the%20late%20first%20millennium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Long%20Conservative%20Turn%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Tantra%20declined%2C%20so%20did%20the%20depictions%20of%20sex%20on%20temple%20walls.%20Little%20of%20this%20style%20of%20art%20was%20commissioned%20after%201400.%20For%20instance%2C%20one%20finds%20very%20little%20sex%20on%20the%20temple%20walls%20of%20Vijayanagar.%20A%20strong%20link%20between%20sex%20and%20religion%20was%20broken.%20Erotic%20visual%20art%20retreated%20to%20private%20spaces%20and%20personal%20objects.%20The%20Kamasutra%20too%20fell%20into%20obscurity.%20Fewer%20Hindus%20now%20had%20casual%20sexual%20escapades%2C%20wrote%20erotic%20poetry%2C%20or%20married%20out%20of%20caste.%20Large%20numbers%20were%20drawn%20to%20Bhakti%20and%20the%20devotional%20ecstasies%20of%20Chaitanya%20Mahaprabhu%2C%20Mirabai%2C%20Eknath%2C%20Tulsidas%2C%20and%20Surdas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20role%20and%20function%20of%20temples%20in%20public%20life%20began%20changing%20to%20mere%20places%20of%20worship%2C%20partly%20also%20as%20their%20wealth%20and%20patronage%20declined%20under%20Indo-Muslim%20rule.%20Tantra%20receded%20to%20the%20fringe%2C%20where%20it%20survives%20to%20this%20day.%20We%20no%20longer%20find%20sex%20on%20modern%20urban%20temples%2C%20but%20we%20can%20still%20see%20sculpture%20like%20this%20in%20a%20recent%20Shiva-Parvati%20temple%20at%20the%20foothills%20of%20Niyamgiri%20Hills%20in%20the%20tribal%20belt%20of%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20decline%20of%20Tantrism%2C%20the%20status%20of%20women%20worsened%20too.%20Control%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20sexuality%20increased%20to%20maintain%20the%20sanctity%20of%20caste.%20The%20goal%20of%20sex%20moved%20closer%20to%20procreation%2C%20as%20in%20the%20Manusmriti.%20In%20parallel%2C%20the%20centrality%20of%20goddesses%20declined%20too%E2%80%94or%20rather%2C%20the%20goddesses%20nominally%20remained%2C%20but%20gradually%20became%20%E2%80%98consorts%E2%80%99%20to%20male%20gods%2C%20basically%2C%20sidekicks.%20They%20became%20sweeter%20and%20tamer.%20Such%20as%20Pampa%2C%20once%20a%20powerful%20tribal%20goddess%20of%20the%20Hampi%20region%20whose%20husband%20Virupaksha%20was%20a%20relatively%20minor%20god%2C%20until%20their%20status%20got%20flipped.%20This%20status%20reversal%20accompanied%20their%20induction%20into%20the%20Brahminical%20pantheon%20as%20forms%20of%20Parvati%20and%20Shiva%E2%80%94an%20increasingly%20common%20story%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20conservative%20turn%20was%20led%20by%20forces%20within%20Hinduism%2C%20long%20before%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Sultanate%20around%201200.%20Of%20course%2C%20Indo-Muslim%20elites%20were%20no%20friends%20of%20Tantra%20either.%20In%20their%20attitudes%20to%20sex%2C%20orthodox%20Hindus%20and%20Bhakti%20saints%20were%20brothers%20under%20the%20skin%20with%20orthodox%20Muslims%20and%20Sufi%20saints.%20So%20were%20the%20Christian%20British%2C%20who%20neither%20helped%20the%20cause%20of%20Tantra%2C%20nor%20fairly%20assessed%20its%20place%20in%20the%20history%20of%20Indian%20religious%20thought.%20With%20Brahmins%20as%20their%20native%20informants%2C%20the%20British%20incorrectly%20placed%20Brahminical%20texts%20at%20the%20core%20of%20historical%20Hinduism.%20This%20suppressed%20the%20awesome%20religious%20diversity%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20surprisingly%2C%20the%20Victorian%20British%20of%20the%20colonial%20era%20rejuvenated%20Hindu%20conservatism.%20We%20got%20men%20like%20Vivekanada%20and%20Gandhi%2C%20with%20their%20famous%20hang-ups%20about%20sex.%20Hindu%20goddesses%20got%20wrapped%20up%20in%20clothes%2C%20and%20artists%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20comply%20were%20harassed%20for%20hurting%20%E2%80%98religious%20sentiments%E2%80%99.%20Such%20prudishness%20would%20have%20drawn%20amused%20laughter%20from%20Khajuraho%E2%80%99s%20religious%20leaders%20a%20thousand%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20reactionary%20Hindu%20nationalists%20make%20vapid%20claims%20about%20a%20sanatan%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98eternal%E2%80%99%2C%20Hindu%20religion%20that%20was%20supposedly%20always%20pure%2C%20chaste%2C%20and%20sexually%20austere.%20They%20rage%20against%20Valentine%E2%80%99s%20Day%2C%20demand%20sexual%20modesty%20from%20women%2C%20and%20even%20harass%20couples%20who%20indulge%20in%20public%20displays%20of%20affection.%20And%20they%20do%20this%2C%20without%20irony%2C%20in%20the%20name%20of%20preserving%20Indian%20tradition!%20One%20imagines%20countless%20medieval%20Indians%20turning%20in%20their%20graves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Fall%20of%20the%20Chandelas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chandelas%20were%20often%20at%20war%20with%20others%E2%80%94the%20Chedis%2C%20Chalukyas%2C%20Chauhans%2C%20and%20once%20even%20the%20formidable%20Mahmud%20of%20Ghazni%2C%20who%20the%20Chandelas%20pushed%20back%20in%201022%E2%80%94an%20event%20they%20celebrated%20by%20commissioning%20their%20grandest%20temple%2C%20the%20Kandariya%20Mahadeva.%20In%20the%2013th%20century%2C%20they%20became%20a%20vassal%20state%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Sultanate%20and%20their%20power%20kept%20declining.%20They%20abandoned%20Khajuraho%20and%20retreated%20to%20a%20distant%20hill%20fort%20(Kalinjar).%20Khajuraho%20was%20no%20longer%20a%20power%20centre%2C%20partly%20why%20its%20temples%20did%20not%20become%20a%20target%20of%20political%20rivals.%20In%20the%2014th%20century%2C%20Khajuraho%20dropped%20out%20of%20history%20and%20public%20memory%2C%20and%20was%20consumed%20by%20the%20forest.%20It%20would%20become%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20%E2%80%98lost%20cities%E2%80%99%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20next%20episode%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20explore%20the%20accounts%20of%20two%20amazing%20travellers%E2%80%94Alberuni%20and%20Marco%20Polo%E2%80%94who%20came%20to%20India%20in%20the%20early%20centuries%20of%20the%20second%20millennium%20and%20made%20insightful%20observations%20about%20Indian%20society%20and%20culture.%20See%20you%20next%20time!%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708769127000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F24152110%2Fimage-1871.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-6-khajuraho-and-the-world-of-tantra%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Discover%20the%20lost%20world%20of%20Khajuraho%2C%20the%20influence%20of%20Tantrism%20in%20early%20medieval%20India%2C%20and%20its%20decline.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-6-khajuraho-and-the-world-of-tantra%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LS%20polls%3A%20Cong%20gives%20Bharuch%20seat%20to%20AAP%3B%20Mumtaz%20reacts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708769096000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107966126%2Cimgsize-43672.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fahmed-patels-legacy-wont-go-in-vain-mumtaz-reacts-after-congress-announces-giving-late-fathers-seat-to-aap%2Farticleshow%2F107965713.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Her%20comments%20came%20soon%20after%20it%20was%20announced%20that%20the%20Bharuch%20constituency%20has%20been%20offered%20to%20the%20Aam%20Adami%20Party%20(AAP)%20as%20part%20of%20the%20seat-share%20pact%20in%20Gujarat.%20Mumtaz%20said%20she%20would%20regroup%20with%20the%20party%20cadre%20to%20make%20the%20Congress%20party%20stronger.%20Mumtaz%20has%20been%20active%20in%20the%20constituency%2C%20which%20is%20viewed%20as%20her%20father%20Ahmed%20Patel's%20bastion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%2